to the editor the massachusetts institute of technology 's plan to put its course material on the web free of charge is an awesome and humbling step front page april 4 true it may be more fun for undergraduates and graduate students to learn in the classroom with mit 's charming quirkiness and intense academic culture but for people with jobs mortgages and children repeating college is n't an option the opportunity to relearn fields that have changed in the decades since we left college is a precious gift i do hope that the home page for this venture includes a discreet one click box so that those of us who choose to support this academic shareware may do so cristina munoz chapel hill nc april 4 2001

